release.body:
## Added

- Add a sidecar build for M1 based Macs [collector-sidecar#428](https://github.com/Graylog2/collector-sidecar/issues/428)
- Add support for multiple configurations on a single collector [collector-sidecar#441](https://github.com/Graylog2/collector-sidecar/issues/441)
- Add tagging support to sidecars [collector-sidecar#441](https://github.com/Graylog2/collector-sidecar/issues/441)
- Add upgrade support and improve Sidecar installer for Windows [collector-sidecar#365](https://github.com/Graylog2/collector-sidecar/issues/365) [collector-sidecar#432](https://github.com/Graylog2/collector-sidecar/issues/432) [collector-sidecar#447](https://github.com/Graylog2/collector-sidecar/issues/447)

## Changed

- Make collector validation timeout configurable [collector-sidecar#431](https://github.com/Graylog2/collector-sidecar/issues/431) [collector-sidecar#435](https://github.com/Graylog2/collector-sidecar/issues/435)



**Full Changelog**: https://github.com/Graylog2/collector-sidecar/compare/1.2.0...1.3.0

payload.description: A collection of open source Graylog integrations that will be released together.
Graylog Processing Pipeline functions to enrich log messages with IoC information from threat intelligence databases
Several bundled Graylog plugins to integrate with different AWS services like CloudTrail and FlowLogs.
Collector plugin for Graylog
Free and open source log management
